snippet: President Obama’s top technology adviser said the failure occurred in the part of the Web site that lets people create user accounts at the beginning of the insurance sign-up process.
abstract: Technical glitches during enrollment cause online health insurance exchanges to crash under weight of millions of users in first week; Pres Obama’s top technology adviser Todd Park says failure occurred in part of Web site that allows people to create user accounts at beginning of insurance sign-up process.

byline.original: By MICHAEL D. SHEAR and ROBERT PEAR
byline.contributor: Quentin Hardy contributed reporting from San Francisco.

lead_paragraph: President Obama’s top technology adviser said the failure occurred in the part of the Web site that lets people create user accounts at the beginning of the insurance sign-up process.

headline.main: Health Exchange Delays Tied to Software Crash in Early Rush
